---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="TGCDN - About ">
  <section class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row w-full h-screen overflow-hidden">
    <aside
      class="hidden lg:block lg:w-64 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 border-r lg:overflow-auto overflow-hidden"
    >
      <nav class="px-4 py-6 space-y-2">
        <a
          class="block px-2 py-1 text-lg font-semibold hover:bg-gray-200 dark:hover:bg-gray-700 rounded"
          href="#"
        >
          Introduction
        </a>
        <a
          class="block px-2 py-1 text-lg font-semibold hover:bg-gray-200 dark:hover:bg-gray-700 rounded"
          href="#"
        >
          Getting Started
        </a>
        <a
          class="block px-2 py-1 text-lg font-semibold hover:bg-gray-200 dark:hover:bg-gray-700 rounded"
          href="#"
        >
          Installation
        </a>
        <a
          class="block px-2 py-1 text-lg font-semibold hover:bg-gray-200 dark:hover:bg-gray-700 rounded"
          href="#"
        >
          Components
        </a>
        <a
          class="block px-2 py-1 text-lg font-semibold hover:bg-gray-200 dark:hover:bg-gray-700 rounded"
          href="#"
        >
          API Reference
        </a>
      </nav>
    </aside>
    <main class="flex-1 p-6 lg:overflow-auto overflow-hidden">
      <article>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Introduction</h1>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Welcome to the documentation page. In this section, you will learn
          about the core concepts of the application...
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Getting Started</h1>
        <p class="mb-4">
          To get started with the application, you need to first install it on
          your system...
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Installation</h1>
        <p class="mb-4">
          You can install the application using the following command...
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Components</h1>
        <p class="mb-4">
          The application consists of several components that you can use to
          build your application...
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">API Reference</h1>
        <p class="mb-4">
          In this section, you will find the complete API reference for the
          application...
        </p>
      </article>
    </main>
  </section>
</Layout>
